  <title><codeph>org.dita.dost.platform.ImportAntLibAction</codeph></title>
  <shortdesc>Creates Ant <xmlelement>pathelement</xmlelement> elements for each file supplied to the
    extension point in the plug-in descriptor file.</shortdesc>
  <refbody>
    <example>
      <title><filepath conref="../resources/conref-task.dita#ID/samples-dir"
          /><filepath>/plugins/com.extension-points.defs</filepath></title>
      <draft-comment author="staylor">
        <fig>
          <title>In <filepath>plugin.xml</filepath></title>
          <codeblock><coderef href="../samples/plugins/com.extension-points.defs/plugin.xml#line=7,9"/></codeblock>
        </fig>
        <fig>
          <title>In <filepath>build_template.xml</filepath></title>
          <codeblock><coderef href="../samples/plugins/com.extension-points.defs/build_template.xml#line=24,37"/></codeblock>
        </fig>
        <fig>
          <title>In <filepath>build.xml</filepath> (after integration)</title>
          <codeblock><coderef href="../samples/plugins/com.extension-points.defs/build.xml#line=17,25"/></codeblock>
        </fig>
      </draft-comment>
    </example>
    <section>
      <title><codeph>dita.conductor.lib.import</codeph></title>
      <p>Use the pre-defined <codeph>dita.conductor.lib.import</codeph> extension point to add Java
        libraries to the DITA-OT <parmname>classpath</parmname> parameter.</p>
    </section>
  </refbody>
